verbose_text: We selected the following genes that are expressed exclusively in the immune system : toll like receptors (TLRs) and downstream signaling molecule mRNA such as myeloid differentiation factor 88 (MyD88), Toll / IL-1 receptor domain containing adaptor inducing IFN-beta (TRIF), inflammatory cytokines including type I interferon (IFN), myxovirus-resistance gene (Mx), tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNFalpha) and interleukin-1beta (IL-1beta), and matrix metalloproteinases (MMP).
evidence: expressed exclusively in the immune system: toll-like receptors
